cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper deals with text mining and natural language processing techniques to analyze the speeches of US Presidents. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves the use of expert systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of web scraping to construct the dataset suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The rank-size analysis used in the paper is a statistical technique, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of social and political nature, which suggests the involvement of the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
